* Task 8a fixture: perform-inline-wins/MAIN.NSP
* Demonstrates that inline DEFINE SUBROUTINE wins over external .NSS.
* Contains BOTH:
*   - An inline DEFINE SUBROUTINE SHARED-SUB
*   - A PERFORM SHARED-SUB statement (should resolve to inline, not external)
*   - An external SHARED-SUB.NSS also exists in the workspace
*
* M-4 (inline-wins): PERFORM resolves to the inline definition first.
* When the inline definition is removed, it should resolve to the external .NSS.

DEFINE DATA
LOCAL
  1 RESULT (A10)
END DEFINE

* Inline subroutine definition (will win over external SHARED-SUB.NSS).
DEFINE SUBROUTINE SHARED-SUB
  MOVE 'INLINE' TO RESULT
END SUBROUTINE

* PERFORM targets the inline subroutine (not the external one).
* Extraction sets the inline match's Target range (non-zero).
* Resolution must NOT re-resolve it to the external NSS.
PERFORM SHARED-SUB

END
